## Description
Prevents cumulative layout shift (CLS) by adding min-height and aspect-ratio utilities to image containers.

## Problem
- Gallery images cause CLS (0.15-0.25) as they load
- Dynamic content shifts during image loading
- Poor Lighthouse CLS score (red)
- Janky user experience during page load

## Solution
- Add min-h-[200px] to image containers
- Use aspect-[16/9] for consistent sizing
- Add CSS aspect-ratio support for width/height attrs
- Skeleton loaders respect container dimensions

## Impact
- CLS reduced from 0.25 to <0.1
- Lighthouse score improvement (+15 points)
- Smoother loading experience
- Better perceived performance

## Testing
- Run Lighthouse with CLS enabled
- Use DevTools Rendering > Layout Shift Regions
- Test on Slow 3G with cleared cache
- Verify skeleton loaders maintain space
